Implement `marketplace-source-manager.ts` which owns CRUD for `~/.dork/marketplaces.json` and seeds the default `dorkos-community` source on first run.

## File

`apps/server/src/services/marketplace/marketplace-source-manager.ts`

## Behavior

- Reads/writes `${dorkHome}/marketplaces.json` (NOT `os.homedir()` — receive `dorkHome` as a constructor parameter; see `.claude/rules/dork-home.md`).
- File schema (validate with zod):

```json
{
  "version": 1,
  "sources": [
    {
      "name": "dorkos-community",
      "source": "https://github.com/dorkos/marketplace",
      "enabled": true,
      "addedAt": "2026-04-06T12:00:00Z"
    }
  ]
}
```

- On first read, if the file doesn't exist, create it seeded with `dorkos-community` and `claude-plugins-official`.
- Atomic writes: write to `marketplaces.json.tmp` then `fs.rename` to avoid corrupted state on crash.

## Public API

```typescript
export class MarketplaceSourceManager {
  constructor(private readonly dorkHome: string) {}

  /** List all configured sources. Seeds defaults on first call if file missing. */
  async list(): Promise<MarketplaceSource[]>;

  /** Get one source by name. Returns null if not found. */
  async get(name: string): Promise<MarketplaceSource | null>;

  /** Add a new source. Throws if name already exists. */
  async add(input: { name: string; source: string; enabled?: boolean }): Promise<MarketplaceSource>;

  /** Remove a source by name. No-op if not found. */
  async remove(name: string): Promise<void>;

  /** Enable/disable a source. */
  async setEnabled(name: string, enabled: boolean): Promise<MarketplaceSource>;
}
```

## Default sources to seed

