Implement `transaction.ts` — the atomic stage→activate→cleanup primitive used by every install flow.

## File

`apps/server/src/services/marketplace/transaction.ts`

## Spec contract (verbatim)

```typescript
// apps/server/src/services/marketplace/transaction.ts
export interface TransactionOptions<T> {
  name: string;
  rollbackBranch: boolean;
  stage: (staging: { path: string }) => Promise<void>;
  activate: (staging: { path: string }) => Promise<T>;
}

export async function runTransaction<T>(
  opts: TransactionOptions<T>
): Promise<T & { rollbackBranch?: string }> {
  const stagingDir = await fs.mkdtemp(path.join(os.tmpdir(), `dorkos-install-${opts.name}-`));
  let backupBranch: string | undefined;

  try {
    // Optional: create a git rollback branch in the user's project (mirrors template-downloader pattern)
    if (opts.rollbackBranch) {
      backupBranch = await createBackupBranch(opts.name);
    }

    // Stage
    await opts.stage({ path: stagingDir });

    // Activate
    const result = await opts.activate({ path: stagingDir });

    // Cleanup staging on success
    await fs.rm(stagingDir, { recursive: true, force: true });

    return { ...result, rollbackBranch: backupBranch };
  } catch (err) {
    // Rollback: clean staging, restore from backup branch if applicable
    await fs.rm(stagingDir, { recursive: true, force: true });
    if (backupBranch) {
      await rollbackToBranch(backupBranch);
    }
    throw err;
  }
}
```

## Backup branch helpers

Look at `apps/server/src/services/core/template-downloader.ts` for the existing backup branch pattern. Extract or copy the same logic — name format `dorkos-install/<name>-<timestamp>`. Both helpers shell out to `git`:

```typescript
async function createBackupBranch(name: string): Promise<string> {
  const branch = `dorkos-install/${name}-${Date.now()}`;
  // git stash --include-untracked
  // git branch <branch> HEAD
  // git stash pop  (if a stash was created)
  return branch;
}

async function rollbackToBranch(branch: string): Promise<void> {
  // git reset --hard <branch>
  // git branch -D <branch>
}
```

If the user's CWD is not a git repo, both helpers should be no-ops (return undefined / silently succeed). Add a small `isGitRepo()` guard.

## Failure-path requirements (acceptance criteria from spec)

- Failed installs leave **zero residual files** on disk.
- Backup branches are created when `rollbackBranch: true` and respected on failure.
- Staging dir is always cleaned up — even if rollback itself fails (use a `finally` in addition to the catch, or wrap rollback in try/catch).

## Tests

Create `apps/server/src/services/marketplace/__tests__/transaction.test.ts`:

- Happy path: `stage` writes a file in staging, `activate` returns a result, transaction returns it. Staging dir is removed.
- `stage` throws → staging dir removed, error rethrown.
- `activate` throws → staging dir removed, error rethrown.
- `rollbackBranch: true` + git repo: `createBackupBranch` invoked, branch passed to `rollbackToBranch` on failure.
- `rollbackBranch: true` + non-git CWD: no backup branch created, no error.
- `activate` succeeds but cleanup fails: error is logged but the transaction result is still returned (don't fail the transaction over a cleanup failure — log and proceed).
- Mock `fs.mkdtemp`, `fs.rm`, and the backup branch helpers via spies.

## Acceptance criteria

- [ ] `runTransaction<T>()` implemented per spec contract
- [ ] Backup branch helpers handle non-git CWDs gracefully
- [ ] Zero residual files on every failure path
- [ ] Tests cover happy path + 4 failure modes
- [ ] TSDoc on every export

Implement `flows/install-plugin.ts` — installs plugin packages by copying contents to `${dorkHome}/plugins/${name}/` (or project-local), compiling extensions, and registering them with `extensionManager`.

## File

`apps/server/src/services/marketplace/flows/install-plugin.ts`

## Spec contract (verbatim)

```typescript
async function installPlugin(
  packagePath: string,
  manifest: PluginPackageManifest,
  opts: InstallRequest
): Promise<InstallResult> {
  const installRoot = opts.projectPath
    ? path.join(opts.projectPath, '.dork/plugins', manifest.name)
    : path.join(dorkHome, 'plugins', manifest.name);

  return runTransaction({
    name: `install-plugin:${manifest.name}`,
    rollbackBranch: true,
    async stage(staging) {
      // Copy package contents to staging
      await fs.cp(packagePath, staging.path, { recursive: true });

      // Compile any extensions inside .dork/extensions/
      const extDir = path.join(staging.path, '.dork/extensions');
      if (await exists(extDir)) {
        for (const ext of await fs.readdir(extDir)) {
          await extensionCompiler.compile(path.join(extDir, ext));
        }
      }
    },
